  Change encoding to UTF-8 for GLEP 31 compliance

  10 Dec 2004; Joseph Jezak <josejx@gentoo.org> :
  Tested and marked ppc stable.

*sox-12.17.6 (20 Nov 2004)

  20 Nov 2004; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> +sox-12.17.6.ebuild:
  Version bump. Upstream changelog mentions .wav segfault bug fixes, PPC users
  please test this.

  12 Nov 2004; Bryan Østergaard <kloeri@gentoo.org> sox-12.17.5-r1.ebuild:
  Stable on alpha.

  18 Oct 2004; Jeremy Huddleston <eradicator@gentoo.org>
  sox-12.17.5-r1.ebuild:
  Stable amd64, sparc, x86.

  18 Oct 2004; Joseph Jezak <josejx@gentoo.org>
  +files/sox-wav-segfault.patch, sox-12.17.4-r2.ebuild,
  sox-12.17.5-r1.ebuild:
  Added -fsigned-char to sox-12.17.4-r2 and sox-12.17.5-r1 to fix bug #35745.
  Patch for wav segfaults in sox-12.17.5-r1, also bug #35745

  14 Sep 2004; Jeremy Huddleston <eradicator@gentoo.org> :
  Removing sox-12.17.5 as it installs exactly the same thing as -r1. -r1 should
  NOT have been added to portage. If you already have sox-12.17.5 installed, you
  will gain nothing by emerging sox-12.17.5-r1.

*sox-12.17.5-r1 (11 Sep 2004)

  11 Sep 2004; Doug Goldstein <cardoe@gentoo.org> +sox-12.17.5-r1.ebuild:
  Disable ALSA support because it's broken in sox. See bug #63531.

  11 Sep 2004; Jeremy Huddleston <eradicator@gentoo.org> sox-12.17.5.ebuild:
  ALSA support is broken... using OSS by default.

